.Dd February 16, 2004
.Dt SPAMDB 8
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm spamdb
.Nd spamd database tool
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm spamdb
.Bk -words
.Op Fl a Ar ip
.Op Fl d Ar ip
.Ek
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
manipulates the spamd database in
.Pa /var/db/spamd
used for
.Xr spamd 8
greylisting.
.Pp
The options are as follows:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl a Ar ip
Add or update a whitelist entry for IP address "ip".
Updates time last seen to now.
.It Fl d Ar ip
Delete a whitelist entry for IP address "ip".
.El
.Pp
If invoked without any arguments,
.Nm
lists the contents of the database
in a text format.
.Sh FILES
/var/db/spamd
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr spamd.conf 5 ,
.Xr spamd 8 ,
.Xr spamd-setup 8
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Nm
command
appeared in
.Ox 3.5 .
